        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-10-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-10-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="493" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d493">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Boutwell</persName>,
                                    Secretary of the Treasury, to Mr. <persName type="to">Rumley</persName>, collector.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Treasury
                                        Department</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-10-07">
                        <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 7,
                                1869</date>.</dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">D. Rumley</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Wilmington, North Carolina:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>War Department has issued orders to Army officers at the fort to
                                assist you. Bring the Hornet under guns of fort. Take such
                                possession of her, and, if necessary, so far dismantle her as to
                                make it impossible for her to go to sea, until you have orders to
                                release her.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GEO. S. BOUTWELL,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of
                                        Treasury.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
